A minimalistic illustration of an empty wooden dock extending into a perfectly still lake at dawn, with a single pair of worn sandals left behind at the dock's edge. Soft mist rises from the water's surface, and in the distance, forested mountains fade into layers of pale blue and lavender. A small backpack sits unopened beside the sandals. The scene is bathed in gentle peach and gold morning light, conveying absolute peace and intentional disconnection. The composition emphasizes vast negative space—the expansive sky and calm water dominating the frame—creating a profound sense of solitude and digital detox. No people visible, just evidence of someone who chose to step away from everything.
